<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 4:58PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Beaver
County through 530 PM CDT...
At 458 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boyd, or 17 miles west of Beaver, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bryans Corner, Balko and Boyd.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
